release.name: v0.2.0
release.body:
## What's Changed
* Add ability to add a component by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/29
* Add pretty url output path by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/30
* Add slugified title by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/31
* Refactor to support AC 2.0 by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/32
* Feature/content permalink by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/33
* Feature/content improvements by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/34
* Revert auto-escaping, add explicit escaping method to context by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/35
* Add renderer to create content for atom feed by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/36
* Improve cli commands, allow profiles by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/37
* Remove turning nested array into context objects by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/38
* Properly wire services into annotated container by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/pull/39


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/cspray/blogisthenics/compare/v0.1.0...v0.2.0

release.body:
This patch resolves a dependency upgrade problem, where the following versions of cspray/annotated-container-adr could not be supported with cspray/annotated-container 2.x:

- 3.2
- 3.3

These releases rely on a version of cspray/annotated-target that is not supported until Annotated Container v3. This patch downgrades required dependencies to use a supported version of Annotated Target.

**If you are using the listed versions of this library, please upgrade to 3.3.1**
